          <Textbox Name="Textbox67">
            <rd:DefaultName>Textbox67</rd:DefaultName>
            <CanGrow>true</CanGrow>
            <KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether>
            <Paragraphs>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>1. Tax Invoice to be sent along with goods. M/s O.P. Jindal Institute of Cancer and Cardiac Research, Order No, Drug License No., GST No., Batch No., PAN No., MRP must be mentioned on all Bills wherever applicable. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>2. Material must be delivered at receiving bay situated in the Central Medical Store/General Store. Receiving time: Monday to Saturday 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>3. Vendors must guarantee that the goods are free from defects and that the import, storage, sales, and use of the goods do not violate any third-party rights. Vendors shall be liable to replace all goods. They must also replace or take back goods that have expired within three months prior or are due to expire within six months, as well as all non-moving stock lying with the hospital. In the event that the vendor does not pick up the goods despite reminders, a debit note and items dispatch note will be prepared and sent via email. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>4. Payment of Invoices not carrying a reference of our Purchase Order number is liable to get delayed and hospital is not liable for any penalty or penal charges for the same. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>5. The hospital would have the sole discretion to approve or reject the delivery of a vendor who does not fulfil the delivery details as per the issued PO without incurring any liability. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>6. Any supply made against Purchase Order, considered as acceptance of terms and conditions as mentioned in the Purchase Order </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>7. Materials less than 6 months’ expiry would not be accepted except for emergency items. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>8. Any dispute pertaining to the purchase order is subject to jurisdiction of Hisar Court. However, any dispute, controversy or claim arising out of or relating to these terms and conditions, or the breach, termination or invalidity thereof, shall be settled by arbitration in accordance with the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996. The seat of arbitration shall be Hisar. The arbitration proceedings shall be conducted in English. The parties agree to appoint a sole arbitrator to be appointed by hospital. The award shall be final and binding on both parties </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>9. The vendor shall ensure compliance with all statutory provisions/ Acts/ Govts circulars and notifications to the extent applicable to them. The hospital will never be held responsible for any compliances/legal requirements that the vendor must fulfil and vendor undertakes to indemnify the Hospital from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorney's fees) arising out of or in connection with any breach of any statutory provisions/ Acts/ Govts circulars and notifications to the extent applicable to vendor</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>Prepared By : </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>8pt</FontSize>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>=First(Fields!SystemCreatedBy.Value, "DataSet_Result")</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontFamily>Segoe UI</FontFamily>
